================================================================================
ORIGINAL WORK DECLARATION
================================================================================

The following are original contributions by Kris Welc, first published
February 28, 2026:

1. The "Agent Algebra" framework concept — mapping six classical mathematical
   theorems to agent composition primitives with formal guarantees.

2. The specific theorem-to-primitive mapping:
   - Banach Fixed-Point Theorem     -> Contraction Mapping primitive
   - Schapire AdaBoost Theorem      -> Cascade primitive
   - de Finetti Proper Scoring Rules -> Calibration primitive
   - Ole Peters Ergodicity Economics -> Kelly Sizing primitive
   - Pearl Belief Propagation       -> Message Passing primitive
   - Kolmogorov MDL Principle       -> Compression Filter primitive

3. The implementation of these primitives as composable, immutable,
   zero-dependency Python modules.

4. Interactive visualizations demonstrating theorem convergence properties.

5. The application of this framework to LLM pipeline orchestration,
   multi-agent systems, and autonomous agent architectures.

