MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATIONS — ATTRIBUTION
================================================================================

The mathematical theorems referenced in this work are established results
from their respective fields. This framework builds upon, but does not claim
ownership of, these foundational results:

- Banach Fixed-Point Theorem (1922)
  Stefan Banach. "Sur les operations dans les ensembles abstraits et leur
  application aux equations integrales." Fundamenta Mathematicae 3: 133-181.

- AdaBoost (1995)
  Yoav Freund and Robert E. Schapire. "A decision-theoretic generalization
  of on-line learning and an application to boosting." Journal of Computer
  and System Sciences 55(1): 119-139.

- Proper Scoring Rules
  Bruno de Finetti (1962). "Does it make sense to speak of 'good probability
  appraisers'?" In The Scientist Speculates, I.J. Good (ed.), pp. 357-364.

- Ergodicity Economics
  Ole Peters (2019). "The ergodicity problem in economics."
  Nature Physics 15: 1216-1221.

- Belief Propagation
  Judea Pearl (1988). "Probabilistic Reasoning in Intelligent Systems:
  Networks of Plausible Inference." Morgan Kaufmann.

- Minimum Description Length
  Andrey Kolmogorov (1963). "On Tables of Random Numbers."
  Sankhya: The Indian Journal of Statistics, Series A 25: 369-376.
  Peter Rissanen (1978). "Modeling by shortest data description."
  Automatica 14(5): 465-471.

